<br>
This is a solid indicator of a &quot;bug&quot; and is extremely unsettling.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
A consistent, repeatable change for the worse could at least be discussed efficently and likely code could be easily modified.<br>
<br>
Instead, this seemingly random, inconsistent weird aggro causes a lot of doubt about not only what is wrong, but even if thier is anything wrong.  And it suggests a difficult code change to even find let alone resolve.<br>
<br>
That said, its clear that the aggro changes have caused some problems, albiet of a not completely repeatable nature.  I call on Sony to admit, in the least, that it is extremely likely that there is a siginifcant bug(s) in aggro at the moment, and work hard on fixing them ASAP.<br>
