<br>
The day after the patch my guild went to Vex Thal.  Okay, now we've done VT a LOT, and every caster there, after several VT runs of 6+ hours killing the same mobs over and over, knows what to expect and where to draw the line on their casting.<br>
<br>
The day after the patch?  Mage crit, Immediately summoned.  Another mage crit, immediately summoned.  Wizard crit, immediately summoned. Another wizard crit, immediately summoned.  <br>
<br>
Mage was just rezzed before Thall Va Kelun, this mage had just been killed by a spell crit, and was rather pissed off, just got Symbol, Po9, c5 focus etc, wasn't low HP, and he was sitting there medding.... Top of the rampage list for the fight. Never even touched TVK. Mage died, got rezzed and gated out and logged out of frustration.<br>
<br>
VT continued like this, I was getting summoned on mobs nuking for the first time at 40% and critting Strike of Solusek.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Then VT ended...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
On to the High Priest Ultor event for the lower CoD/Bertox key.<br>
Raex and Vindor. Two mobs that are exactly alike, back to back.  We fought them the same way, warrior with 2 EB weapons runs up and uses their riposte discipline and everyone else Zergs like there' sno tomorrow. (If you don't know what Zerg means, /boggle, everyone threw out as much damage as possible with no regards to aggro control)  On Raex, I landed Strike of Solusek for ~3k, then landed a SoS crit for 6k+ and got immediately summoned and eaten.  (That quadding for 1400+ and 5000 lifetap rather suck.)<br>
<br>
I get rezzed and ready, only partially buffed because I figure the same thing's gonna happen...  Landed full 6 non-crit Strikes of Solusek back to back chaining without ever aggroing.  Same tactic as before.<br>
<br>
Can someone explain that?<br>
<br>
&lt;==EDIT==&gt;<br>
